{"id": 7702, "title": "Ticket #7702: Add per-submitter ceiling to limit cores given to a particular submitt", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe only way to put an upper bound on how many slots (cores, etc.) a given submitter can get is by creating accounting groups with quotas.  LIGO would like a per-submitter limit, including the ability to limit a submitter to 0 cores.  Unlike the current fair-share limit, startd RANK would not allow a submitter to go over their limit.  We also need to make sure that when the negotiator limits a submitter, an appropriate message is sent to the schedd so that condor_q -analyze knows what's going on.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2020-Jul-21 10:13:48 by pfc:</em> <br/>\n\nGiven our real-world goal (to start all users with a conservative limit, e.g., 100, and then manually \"promote\" specific users to a higher limit), it might be better if this was <strong>unset</strong> by default, with a default specified in another config variable, which can be overridden on a per-user basis as we see fit.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7837\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7837'); return false;\" title=\"condor_userprio -all display ceiling values\">#7837</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\ncondor_userprio -all display ceiling values</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Sep-30 10:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> 